transcript:
{
 "date": "2023-03-08",
 "time": "10:00 AM",
 "attendess": [
  "Manager",
  "Junior Developer 1",
  "Junior Developer 2",
  "Junior Developer 3"
 ],
 "transcript": "Manager: Good morning, team. Let's start our daily standup meeting. Junior Developer 1, what did you complete yesterday?

Junior Developer 1: I completed the design for the new homepage. I also started working on the front-end development.

Manager: Great work. What are you planning to work on today?

Junior Developer 1: I'll continue working on the front-end development. I'll also start working on the back-end API for the homepage.

Manager: Sounds good. Junior Developer 2, what did you complete yesterday?

Junior Developer 2: I completed the database schema for the new application. I also started working on the back-end API for the user management module.

Manager: Good job. What are you planning to work on today?

Junior Developer 2: I'll continue working on the back-end API for the user management module. I'll also start working on the front-end for the login page.

Manager: Excellent. Junior Developer 3, what did you complete yesterday?

Junior Developer 3: I completed the unit tests for the authentication module. I also started working on the integration tests for the user management module.

Manager: Keep up the good work. What are you planning to work on today?

Junior Developer 3: I'll continue working on the integration tests for the user management module. I'll also start working on the front-end for the dashboard page.

Manager: Perfect. Does anyone have any blockers or challenges they're facing?

Junior Developer 1: I'm having some trouble with the front-end styling. I'm not sure how to achieve the desired look and feel.

Manager: I can help you with that. I have some experience with front-end styling. We can discuss it after the meeting.

Junior Developer 2: I'm having some trouble understanding the requirements for the API. I'm not sure what data I need to return from the endpoints.

Manager: Let's go through the requirements together. I'll clarify any ambiguities.

Junior Developer 3: I'm facing some issues with the integration tests. The tests are failing for some reason. I'm not sure what the problem is.

Manager: Let's debug the tests together. We'll find the root cause of the problem.

Manager: That's it for today's standup meeting. Keep up the good work, and please let me know if you have any questions or concerns.

Junior Developers: Thank you, Manager."
}

```
  "date": "2023-03-08",

    "John Doe (Manager)",
    "Jane Smith (Junior Developer)",

    "Sarah Miller: Sure, Michael. I can help you get started with writing integration tests.",
    "John Doe: Thank you, Sarah. That's very helpful.",
    "John Doe: Alright, everyone. Thank you for your updates. Let's continue working on our tasks and we'll meet again tomorrow for our next standup meeting."
  ]
}
```

  "Junior Developer 1",
  "Junior Developer 2"
 ],
 "transcript": [
  "Manager: Good morning, everyone. Let's start our daily standup meeting.",
  "Junior Developer 1: Hi, everyone. Yesterday, I completed the development of the new product page. Today, I'll be working on integrating the payment gateway.",
  "Junior Developer 2: Hello, team. Yesterday, I finished fixing the bugs in the checkout process. Today, I'll be working on improving the performance of the website.",
  "Manager: Great work, everyone. I'm glad to see that you're all making progress on your tasks.",
  "Junior Developer 1: I do have one question though. I'm not sure how to integrate the payment gateway.",
  "Manager: That's okay. I can help you with that. Just let me know when you're ready.",
  "Junior Developer 2: I'm also facing a bit of a blocker. The website is taking too long to load.",
  "Manager: I see. I'll have to look into that. In the meantime, see if you can identify any specific areas that are causing the slow down.",
  "Junior Developer 2: Sure, I'll do that.",
  "Manager: Alright, everyone. That's all for today's meeting. Keep up the good work.",
  "Junior Developer 1 and 2: Thanks, Manager."
 ]
}

{
    "date": "2022-08-23",
    "time": "10:00 AM",
    "attendess": ["Manager", "Junior 1", "Junior 2", "Junior 3", "Junior 4"],
    "transcript": "**Manager:** Good morning, team. Let's start our daily standup meeting. Junior 1, can you tell us what you worked on yesterday and what you're planning to do today?

**Junior 1:** Yesterday, I finished working on the user interface for the login and registration screens. Today, I'll start working on the backend code for the login and registration functionality.

**Manager:** Great. Junior 2, what about you?

**Junior 2:** I completed the integration of the payment gateway yesterday. Today, I'll start working on the push notification feature.

**Manager:** Excellent. Junior 3, what was your progress yesterday?

**Junior 3:** I worked on the design of the home screen and the product listing pages. Today, I'll start working on the checkout process.

**Manager:** That's great progress. Junior 4, what did you work on yesterday?

**Junior 4:** I finished working on the API integration for the product catalog. Today, I'll start working on the search functionality.

**Manager:** Perfect. Does anyone have any blockers or challenges they're facing?

**Junior 1:** I'm having some trouble with the integration of the social media login feature.

**Manager:** I see. Can you share your screen so we can take a look at it together?

**Junior 1:** Sure. (Shares screen)

**Manager:** (Reviews code) I think I see the issue. You're using the wrong API key.

**Junior 1:** Oh, you're right. I'll fix that now.

**Manager:** Great. Is there anything else?

**Junior 2:** I'm having a hard time understanding the documentation for the push notification feature.

**Manager:** I can help with that. I'll send you a link to some resources that might be helpful.

**Junior 2:** Thank you.

**Manager:** Okay, team. That's all for today. Keep up the good work!

**Meeting adjourned.**"
}
